# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Picsou — Docker environment
#
# Zero-config first boot:
#   Leave everything below unset and `docker compose up` just works. The
#   app entrypoint auto-generates JWT_SECRET, CRYPTO_ENCRYPTION_KEY, and
#   POSTGRES_PASSWORD on first launch (persisted to the `picsou_data`
#   named volume under /data/.secrets/), and the setup wizard at
#   http://localhost:8080 collects the rest interactively.
#
# Advanced: any value set here overrides the auto-generated one. Useful
# for CI, external secret managers, or keeping secrets out of the named
# volume (e.g. if you manage them with Vault).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Database (defaults: picsou/picsou/<auto-generated>)
POSTGRES_DB=picsou
POSTGRES_USER=picsou
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=         # leave blank → auto-generated to /data/.secrets/postgres_password

# Secrets (auto-generated on first boot if left blank)
# JWT_SECRET=                # openssl rand -base64 48
# CRYPTO_ENCRYPTION_KEY=     # openssl rand -base64 32

# App credentials — leave blank to create them via the setup wizard on first launch.
# Only set these if you want to seed an admin programmatically (CI, automated installs).
# APP_USERNAME=admin
# APP_PASSWORD_HASH=$2a$12$REPLACE_THIS_WITH_REAL_BCRYPT_HASH

# CORS — leave blank to configure via the wizard (auto-detected from browser origin).
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://your-nas-ip:8080

# Enable Banking — configure via the wizard's guided flow. Only set manually if you
# already have PSD2 credentials and a generated key pair.
# ENABLEBANKING_APPLICATION_ID=
# ENABLEBANKING_KEY_ID=
# ENABLEBANKING_REDIRECT_URI=http://your-nas-ip:8080/sync/callback
# ENABLEBANKING_PRIVATE_KEY=-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIE...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----

# BoursoBank sidecar (optional override — defaults to http://bourso-auth:8001)
# BOURSO_AUTH_URL=http://bourso-auth:8001

# Secure cookies — set to false when serving over plain HTTP (no TLS terminator).
# The wizard auto-detects this from the browser's protocol.
# SECURE_COOKIES=true

# Spring profile
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod
